President Donald Trump has declared a major disaster in the state of South Carolina due to the impact of Hurricane Irma. This declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. Federal funding will be available for emergency work and the repair or replacement of damaged facilities. The counties of Allendale, Anderson, Bamberg, Barnwell, Beaufort, Berkeley, Charleston, Colleton, Dorchester, Edgefield, Georgetown, Hampton, Jasper, McCormick, Oconee, and Pickens are eligible for this assistance. Additionally, federal funding will be available for hazard mitigation measures statewide. Warren J. Riley has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. Further designations may be made if requested by the state and based on damage assessments. For more information, the FEMA News Desk can be contacted at (202) 646-3272 or FEMA-NEWS-DESK@FEMA.DHS.GOV.